'''Oluf Gabriel Lund''' (8 May 1873 &ndash; 29 November 1966) was a Norwegian military officer.
He was born in [[Oslo|Christiania]], and graduated from the [[Norwegian Military Academy|Military Academy]] in 1897. He was promoted to captain in 1902, major in 1917, lieutenant colonel in 1924, and colonel in 1929. From 1929 he was in command of the Norwegian 10th Infantry Regiment. In a German court-martial in 1940 Lund was sentenced to death. This was later changed to five years {{lang|de|Festunghaftstrafe}}, and he was released in 1943.<ref name=heh-48>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1948|title=Lund, Oluf Gabriel|encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor=Steenstrup, Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1948/0333.html |page=133 |language=Norwegian |accessdate=17 April 2013}}</ref>
Among his works is ''Historik for Fjordane regiment'' from 1931, and ''Dødsdømt'' from 1945. He was decorated Knight of the [[Order of the Dannebrog]].<ref name=heh-48/>
He died in November 1966.<ref name=heh-68>{{cite book|year=1968|title=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|chapter=Fortegnelse over personer som siste gang er omtalt i utgaven 1964 med angivelse av deres dødsdatum|editor=Steenstrup, Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo |page=623|language=Norwegian }}</ref>
